# Project Context

Physiotherapist-focused mini CRM SaaS. Core product: contacts, notes, statuses, appointments, session packages, follow-ups, reports. WhatsApp/Instagram are **provider adapters**, not the domain center.

## Stack

- Next.js App Router, React, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS
- Supabase Postgres/Auth + RLS (planned)
- Vercel (planned)

## MVP order (do not skip)

1. Phase 0 — Foundation (auth, workspace, layout)
2. Phase 1 — Manual CRM (no real messaging APIs)
3. Phase 2 — Physio features (appointments, packages)
4. Phase 3+ — WhatsApp BSP/provider, then Instagram manual pilot, then API integrations

## Forbidden early work

- Direct Meta WhatsApp/Instagram API integration
- Omnichannel inbox before manual CRM is usable
- Auto-merge contacts across channels by name alone
- AI auto-replies or medical advice without human approval
- Installing packages or implementing CRM features unless explicitly requested

## Read before planning

1. `AGENTS.md` — agent behavior source of truth
2. `docs/PROCESS.md`, `docs/TASKS.md`, `docs/DECISIONS.md`
3. Relevant `docs/*.md` and `docs/tasks/PHASE-*.md` for the current phase
4. `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing Next.js code (breaking changes vs training data)
